Hypotheses 
H1 . Fragmented Information Increases Response Time
If sales executives must search across multiple systems (PDFs, spreadsheets, WhatsApp, colleagues, site office), then their client response time will increase significantly, reducing overall sales efficiency.
H2 . Lack of Real-Time Data Reduces Client Trust
If availability and pricing data are not updated in real time, then clients will encounter inconsistencies, causing a decline in trust and lowering conversion rates.
H3 . Inconsistent Data Leads to Sales Errors
If different platforms contain conflicting information, then sales staff are more likely to provide incorrect answers, leading to lost deals.
H4 . Dependency on Colleagues Reduces Operational Reliability
If new or less-experienced staff depend heavily on colleagues for accurate information, then workflow reliability will drop whenever experienced staff are unavailable.
H5 . Cognitive Overload Reduces Sales Performance
If sales executives are required to memorize large volumes of project/plot/pricing details without system support, then cognitive load will increase, negatively affecting performance and confidence.
H6 . Poor Onboarding Slows Learning Curve
If onboarding lacks structure, practice scenarios and centralized learning resources, then new employees will take longer to become independent and effective.
H7 . Lack of Visual Tools Weakens Client Understanding
If project information is primarily text-based without visual maps or interactive tools, then clients will struggle to understand options clearly, reducing engagement and trust.
H8 . System Slowness Reduces Conversion Rates
If internal systems are slow or lag during high-demand periods (weekends), then customer experience will worsen, decreasing the likelihood of successful conversions.
H9 . Repetition Without Automation Wastes Time
If staff must repeatedly answer the same client questions without automated FAQs or standardized responses, then their productivity will decrease and service quality will become inconsistent.
H10 . Departmental Communication Gaps Cause Misinformation
If sales, site office and legal teams are not synchronized in their updates, then clients will receive conflicting or outdated information, harming brand credibility.
H11 . Version Control Issues Create Operational Risk
If multiple versions of the same document exist across different platforms, then staff will frequently rely on outdated files, increasing the chance of incorrect communication.
H12 . High Pressure Leads to Hesitation and Lost Sales
If sales executives feel pressured to respond instantly without accurate tools, then hesitation and uncertainty during conversations will negatively impact customer experience and conversion.
H13 . Absence of a Centralized Platform Drives Inefficiency
If there is no single, integrated information platform, then workflow fragmentation will continue to create delays, errors and emotional stress.
H14 .Accuracy Is the Primary Driver of Sales Confidence
If a system provides consistently accurate information, then sales executives will feel more confident, leading to smoother interactions and higher conversion rates.
